getting set for a chat; he preferred to stand or keep loitering between bed and table, table and sink. Several fir needles lay scattered about the colorless carpet. Suddenly the faint hissing ceased.

“Prussak kaput,” said Serafim.

“We’ll fix that,” Lev began in haste, “just one second.”

But there was no alcohol left in the bottle. “Stupid situation.… You know, I’ll go get some from the landlady.”

